First Read: 14-Jan-26
HB213 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama State Port Authority; to amend
5 Section 33-1-2, Code of Alabama 1975; to authorize the Code
6 Commissioner to change references to the State Port Authority,
7 the Alabama State Docks Department, and the Alabama State Port
8 Authority to the Alabama Port Authority; to repeal Chapter 13
9 of Title 33, consisting of Sections 33-13-1 through 33-13-13,
10 Code of Alabama 1975, to terminate the Alabama Port Authority.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. Section 33-1-2, Code of Alabama 1975, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 "§33-1-2
15 (a) There shall be a state agency known as the Alabama
16 State Port Authority, hereinafter sometimes referred to as the
17 port authority. Notwithstanding any other provision of law,
18 whenever any act, section of this code, or any other provision
19 of law refers to the Alabama State Docks Department, or the
20 Alabama State Port Authority it shall be deemed a reference to
21 the Alabama State Port Authority.
22 (b) The port authority shall promote, supervise,
23 control, manage, and direct the state docks and all other
24 state lands included within the jurisdiction of this chapter
25 and shall maintain and operate all the improvements and
26 facilities authorized by this chapter. The port authority is a
27 body corporate and shall be constituted as provided in this
28 chapter."
Page 1

chapter."
HB213 Enrolled
29 Section 2. The Code Commissioner, at times determined
30 appropriate, shall change all references to the State Port
31 Authority, the Alabama State Docks Department, and the Alabama
32 State Port Authority in the Code of Alabama 1975, to the
33 Alabama Port Authority.
34 Section 3. Chapter 13 of Title 33, consisting of
35 Sections 33-13-1 through 33-13-13, Code of Alabama 1975, which
36 established the Alabama Port Authority, is repealed, thereby
37 terminating the Alabama Port Authority because the Alabama
38 Port Authority is an obsolete entity.
39 Section 4. This act shall become effective immediately.
Page 2

Section 4. This act shall become effective immediately.
